FT  02 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Pipeline fittings buy for Alumasc
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Alumasc, a designer, manufacturer and marketer of products for the brewery,
building and construction industries, has paid Pounds 2m in cash and loan
notes for Superior Pipeline Fittings, a specialist maker of pipeline
fittings for the water industry.
An additional Pounds 1m is dependent on profits. Superior had net assets of
Pounds 500,000 at April 5 and net borrowings of Pounds 150,000.
For the 55 weeks ended April 5 pre-tax profits totalled Pounds 460,000.
