<HEADLINE>
FT  02 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Cost control gives lift to Macfarlane
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
STRICT control over costs helped Macfarlane Group (Clansman) lift profits 13
per cent in the first half of 1992.
On static turnover of Pounds 42.4m (Pounds 42.2m), pre-tax profits were
Pounds 4.55m (Pounds 4.02m).
Earnings per share rose to 6.06p (5.33p) and the interim dividend is
increased from 1.75p to 1.88p.
Lord Macfarlane, chairman of the Glasgow-based packaging company, said that
strict cost controls would ensure the improvements would continue despite
'the recession lasting longer than the economists, and others who should
have known better, predicted.'
At the end of the period the company had no borrowings and cash in hand of
Pounds 6m.
</TEXT>
