<HEADLINE>
FT  02 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Haynes Publishing shows sharp advance to
Pounds 2.37m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
HAYNES PUBLISHING Group, the Somerset-based printer of workshop manuals,
staged a sharp recovery over the 12 months to May 31.
Profits before tax amounted to Pounds 2.37m, against just Pounds 26,000 in
the previous year, on turnover ahead at Pounds 21.2m (Pounds 19.2m).
Mr John Haynes, chairman, said a 'solid' performance in North America had
supported the group during the restructuring of its UK operation.
Exceptional charges of Pounds 928,000 (Pounds 957,000) reflected the
cost-cutting programme in the UK which saw the volume of titles fall by 45
per cent and 25 per cent of the workforce made redundant.
The charge also included costs of writing off unearned royalty balances and
production costs.
Mr Haynes said the elimination of non-recurring costs helped the US
businesses record a 58 per cent profits improvement in dollar terms. The US
side ended the year in a cash positive position, he added.
Overall borrowings were cut from Pounds 4m to Pounds 1.3m over the year,
with gearing falling from 47 per cent to 14 per cent. Interest charges
amounted to Pounds 396,000 (Pounds 566,000).
Reflecting the recovery, earnings per share emerged at 14.5p(0.1p); a
proposed final dividend of 3.5p brings the total for the year to 6p (2.5p).
</TEXT>
