<TEXT>
SIX EUROPEAN aircraft makers have grouped to produce a maritime patrol
aircraft. The initiative comes from Dassault Aviation of France and British
Aerospace, with Deutsche Aerospace of Germany, Construcciones Aeronauticas
(CASA) of Spain, Alenia of Italy and Fokker of the Netherlands.
Through a new 'industrial group', Europatrol, they plan to seek government
