be suitable for updating current aircraft.
France has been pressing for a joint maritime patrol project through the
Independent European Programme Group (IEPG), made up of Nato members. The
companies will lobby governments to set up an outline IEPG 'staff target'
for the aircraft. The UK has been considering Dassault's Atlantique 2 as an
option to replace its ageing Nimrod patrol aircraft.
