<HEADLINE>
FT  02 SEP 92 / Manila hopes rain will aid economy
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MANILA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Philippines economy was almost flat in the first half of the year
because of electricity shortages and a drought in the south, Reuter reports
from Manila.
Officials said the economy may improve in the second half as the onset of
rains had broken a drought covering southern Mindanao island and helped
arrest the power crisis. Real gross national product grew by a slight 0.48
per cent, according to the government.
