<HEADLINE>
FT  02 SEP 92 / Review of fines for late VAT
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CUSTOMS and Excise has launched a review of its default surcharge system for
companies that do not pay value added tax contributions on time, after
criticisms of its operation.
The review comes as part of a wider examination of the VAT penalties system
announced earlier this year. It will examine the effectiveness of the system
of progressive penalties - designed to encourage timely compliance.
The system has been criticised as indiscriminate, providing insufficient
warning before fines are incurred, and for being particularly hard on small
businesses.
VAT Default Surcharge Consultation Paper. HM Customs and Excise, VAT
Enforcement Division, St John's House, Merton Road, Bootle, L20 3NN.
</TEXT>
