FT  01 SEP 92 / Letter: Insulting by numbers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr KHALID AZIZ
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Pakistanis' dislike of the number 420 (Observer, August 24) is based
not on any code describing swindlers but on Pakistan's criminal code, where
the relevant clause is, indeed, number 420. About the worst you can say of a
businessman is that he is a char saw bees aadmi - a 420 man.
Perhaps, in view of the difficulties on the UK financial scene in recent
years, one might be able to refer to relevant clauses from the Financial
Services Act or other laws to describe dubious individuals one encounters]
Khalid Aziz,
chairman,
Aziz Corporation,
West Stratton,
Winchester SO21 3DR
</TEXT>
