FT  01 SEP 92 / International Company News: Cominco sells mine stake
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD SIMON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
COMINCO, the Vancouver-based metals and fertiliser producer, has sold its 46
per cent stake in Australia's Aberfoyle mining and exploration group for
CDollars 135m (USDollars 113.4m), writes Bernard Simon in Toronto.
The buyers are various Australian and international institutions which have
been pressing Cominco for almost a year to part with at least a portion of
its stake in Aberfoyle.
The approaches were initially turned down, but were given consideration as
Aberfoyle's share price rose from less than ADollars 4 to its present level
of more than ADollars 5 a share.
The Canadian company expects to use the proceeds to help finance projects in
Chile, Mexico and, possibly, Turkey. Cominco is committed to providing
USDollars 110m in equity for the Quebrada Blanca copper mine in northern
Chile.
