FT  01 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Stanelco makes Pounds 80,000 profit
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Over the 14 months ended February 28 1992, Stanelco made a pre-tax profit of
Pounds 80,000. That included seven months from the subsidiary Stanelco
Products, maker of induction heating and welding equipment.
The group formerly traded as Merchant Manufactory Estate Company, and was
reorganised at the end of last year. In 1991 the old group incurred an
operating loss of Pounds 1.58m, to which was added exceptional charges of
Pounds 11.6m.
Earnings per share were 0.02p (46.85p).
