FT  29 AUG 92 / UK Company News: Gerald Ratner's total pay listed as Pounds
574,452
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANGUS FOSTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR GERALD RATNER, who earlier this year was forced to step down as chairman
of Ratners jewellery chain after the company ran into financial
difficulties, received total emoluments of Pounds 574,452 in the year to
March 1.
Although this represented a 7 per cent pay cut from the previous year, the
payment came in a year when Ratners reported a loss before tax of Pounds
122m compared with a profit of Pounds 112m, when ordinary shareholders
received no final dividend and when preference shareholders saw their
dividends deferred.
Mr Ratner is also, apparently, receiving the same salary in his remaining
role of chief executive as he received in his previous position as chairman
and managing director.
This is in spite of turning over his responsibilities as executive chairman
to Mr James McAdam who took up the post on January 10.
According to Ratner's annual report, which is due to arrive on shareholders'
desks in coming days, Mr Ratner received Pounds 541,401 in the 11 months
before he gave up the chairmanship, equivalent to Pounds 1,573.86 a day.
In the 21 days left before the accounts were drawn up, Mr Ratner received
Pounds 33,051, equivalent to Pounds 1,573.86 a day.
Meanwhile, Mr McAdam was paid Pounds 15,377 for the period, equivalent to a
more modest Pounds 732.24 a day.
Mr McAdam was not returning telephone calls yesterday to comment on whether
he and Mr Ratner will continue on the same remuneration terms this year.
